-Blue Sad Cookies:
-Base Ingredients
320 g all-purpose flour
220 g light brown sugar
50 g granulated sugar
16 tbsp unsalted butter
-Flavor Ingredients
1.0 tsp mandarin orange zest
340 g chocolate
---
Instructions
Step 1: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F.
Step 2: Mix together dry ingredients, combining flour, ,mandarin orange zest in a large bowl. In another bowl, cream together light brown sugar, granulated sugar and unsalted butter, then add 
Step 3: Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing well. Once mixed, add the chocolate.
Step 4: Let the mixture rest for 4 hours in the refrigerator. On a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, add 50 grams of dough, rolled into a sphere. Bake for 11 minutes, turning the sheet around halfway through the baking time.
Step 5: Let the cookies cool.